  "text": "Jerome Thomas / How-To Geek JBL Xtreme 4 Connectivity Bluetooth 5.3 with Auracast Weight 4.6lbs Battery 24 hours Ports USB-C JBL’s Xtreme 4 portable Bluetooth speaker is getting a big discount of 34%. You can get this powerful speaker, which usually sells for $380, for just $249.95 on Amazon. That’s a huge $130 discount and the lowest price it has ever been on Amazon. When we reviewed the JBL Xtreme 4, we pointed out its audio system with dual subwoofers, two drivers, and dual bass radiators. This setup delivers great sound with deep bass and detail. JBL’s AI-powered optimization helps refine the sound, which reduces distortion even at max volume, so you can turn up your favorite songs without losing clarity. One of the biggest selling points is the Xtreme 4’s long battery life. Its 24-hour replaceable battery means you can enjoy music all day without stopping. If you’re in a hurry, just 10 minutes of charging gives you an extra two hours of playtime. Beyond just playing music, the Xtreme 4 can also work as a power bank, letting you charge your phone or other devices on the go. Durability is another strong feature. The Xtreme 4 has an IP67 rating, meaning it’s completely waterproof and dustproof. This tough design makes it a great choice for beach trips, camping, and other outdoor adventures. For easy carrying, the speaker comes with a shoulder strap, so you can take it anywhere comfortably. You can also connect multiple Xtreme 4 speakers for a bigger and better sound experience. While the Xtreme 4 doesn't have the aux input that was in the Xtreme 3, it does have an Auracast button. This would allow for multi-speaker linking, but not many devices use this yet. However, the aux cable is a bit dated, especially with Bluetooth more widely used, so it's not much of a loss. You can get this great speaker for just $249.95 on Amazon, which is a huge 34% discount. If you wait until the sale is over, you'll have to buy it for $380, so acting fast may be the best strategy.",
