003e\n                \n        \n        \n                    \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eJBL’s Xtreme 4 portable Bluetooth speaker is getting a big discount of 34%. You can get this powerful speaker, which usually sells for $380, for just \u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/JBL-Xtreme-Waterproof-PartyBoost-Multi-speaker/dp/B0CTP191Z3/?tag=hotoge-20\u0026amp;ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2012885\u0026amp;asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fjbls-xtreme-4-waterproof-speaker-is-at-its-lowest-price-ever%2F\u0026amp;asc_campaign=Affiliate\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow\"\u003e$249.95 on Amazon\u003c/a\u003e. That’s a huge $130 discount and the lowest price it has ever been on Amazon.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWhen we \u003ca href=\"https://www.howtogeek.com/jbl-xtreme-4-review/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ereviewed the JBL Xtreme 4\u003c/a\u003e, we pointed out its audio system with dual subwoofers, two drivers, and dual bass radiators. This setup delivers great sound with deep bass and detail. JBL’s AI-powered optimization helps refine the sound, which reduces distortion even at max volume, so you can turn up your favorite songs without losing clarity.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eOne of the biggest selling points is the Xtreme 4’s long battery life. Its 24-hour replaceable battery means you can enjoy music all day without stopping. If you’re in a hurry, just 10 minutes of charging gives you an extra two hours of playtime. Beyond just playing music, the Xtreme 4 can also work as a power bank, letting you charge your phone or other devices on the go.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eDurability is another strong feature. The Xtreme 4 has an \u003ca href=\"https://www.howtogeek.com/62529/ip-ratings-explained-what-does-the-code-mean-for-your-devices/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eIP67 rating\u003c/a\u003e, meaning it’s completely waterproof and dustproof. This tough design makes it a great choice for beach trips, camping, and other outdoor adventures. For easy carrying, the speaker comes with a shoulder strap, so you can take it anywhere comfortably. You can also connect multiple Xtreme 4 speakers for a bigger and better sound experience.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eWhile the Xtreme 4 doesn\u0026#39;t have the aux input that was in the Xtreme 3, it does have an Auracast button. This would allow for multi-speaker linking, but not many devices use this yet. However, the aux cable is a bit dated, especially with Bluetooth more widely used, so it\u0026#39;s not much of a loss.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eYou can get this great speaker for just \u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/JBL-Xtreme-Waterproof-PartyBoost-Multi-speaker/dp/B0CTP191Z3/?tag=hotoge-20\u0026amp;ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2012885\u0026amp;asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fjbls-xtreme-4-waterproof-speaker-is-at-its-lowest-price-ever%2F\u0026amp;asc_campaign=Affiliate\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow\"\u003e$249.95 on Amazon\u003c/a\u003e, which is a huge 34% discount. If you wait until the sale is over, you\u0026#39;ll have to buy it for $380, so acting fast may be the best strategy.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n    \n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
